responses: {"Q0":"It was interesting, i thought i had it figured out in the first half, but then they took a lot of coins away so i changed my approach. I think this is a very simple experiment but yet very functional. I think this tests your ability in recognizing patterns. ","Q1":"First i didn't pick the blue box at all, because it gave me a penalty each time. \nAt first i chose really randomly, but i figured the pattern out and stuck by the red box. I thought this is it so i kept spamming my mouse, of course this wasn't the way so i changed and clicked multiple boxes but not random anymore, i tried to figure out the pattern. I switched between the green, purple and red one, until i got a penalty. My curiosity took the lead and i clicked the blue box just to see what would happen.\nI gained 100 coins so i thought by myself, i just need to keep changing each box everytime and eventually i will reach 3000 coins and this worked for me."}
